Well, we look forward
to seeing that.

00:26:59.190 --> 00:27:01.940
And there are so many
dichotomies in your work,

00:27:01.940 --> 00:27:05.500
including this sort of play
with reality versus sort

00:27:05.500 --> 00:27:11.350
of these more magical,
fantastical sort

00:27:11.350 --> 00:27:13.750
of aesthetics that you even
bring into "Oum Kulthum."

00:27:13.750 --> 00:27:19.510
And there is a sort of tension
between the beauty and also

00:27:19.510 --> 00:27:23.770
the undercurrent of what
you're having to say.

00:27:23.770 --> 00:27:25.840
SHIRIN NESHAT: I think
you put your finger

00:27:25.840 --> 00:27:27.310
